  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Using the power of football to fight HIV/AIDS</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will train 10 players at Livingstone Youth Football Academy (LYFA) to be Sexual Health Football Coaches. They will go into local communities to raise awareness and increase knowledge of HIV/AIDS &amp; other Sexual and Reproductive Health Rights (SRHR) in vulnerable young people in Livingstone, Zambia. The players will undergo training before conducting weekly sessions in local communities in a 1-year project. We will also host football tournaments to promote voluntary HIV testing.</narrative>
  </description>
